## Connecting This Register to Previous Work

The system-level risk register maps directly to the enterprise risk register built on Day 25. The enterprise ransomware risk (MYC-002) becomes RS-001 at the system level. The insider access risk (MYC-005) becomes RS-004. The continuity risk (MYC-001) is addressed by RS-006. This vertical alignment — enterprise risks driving system-level risk scenarios — is a sign of a coherent GRC program rather than disconnected exercises at different levels.

The risk response actions also connect to the continuous monitoring strategy from Day 30. The monitoring activities documented there — GuardDuty review, audit log review, access reviews, backup testing — are precisely the ongoing activities that maintain visibility into the residual risks documented here after mitigation. The risk register and the monitoring strategy are two halves of the same ongoing risk management program.

