## What I Am Still Thinking About

One question that came up today is how to communicate this risk register to the Authorizing Official in a way that generates resource commitment rather than just acknowledgment.

A table of risk IDs and NIST ratings is technically accurate but not inherently compelling to a clinic director or medical director whose primary frame of reference is patient care and organizational finances. The case needs to be made in terms they connect to — the UHS $67 million recovery cost, the Scripps Health month-long outage, the Vermont Medical Center $63 million incident. The mitigation investments required for RS-001 through RS-005 are modest compared to those outcomes.

Translating risk register findings into executive-level risk communication is a core GRC skill I want to continue developing throughout this project. The analysis is the foundation — but the communication is what gets the controls implemented.

